The paper proposes a method for providing interpretable explanations for predictions made by Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) on graph-based machine learning tasks. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are all relevant sub-categories for this paper. Given that the paper focuses on explaining predictions made by GNNs, which are commonly used in graph-based machine learning tasks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, since the paper also discusses the application of the proposed method on real-world tasks, cs.CL, cs.SI, and cs.CV are also possible sub-categories.
